      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(control-ui): attach token query param to avatar URL to fix 401 on Tailscale",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen the Control UI is accessed via Tailscale (cross-origin relative to the gateway), the browser cannot forward `Authorization: Bearer <token>` headers for avatar fetch requests. This causes `GET /avatar/main` to return `401 Unauthorized` even when the user is fully authenticated with a valid gateway session.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe Control UI routes avatar URLs through `buildAssistantAvatarRoute()` which produces paths like `/avatar/main`. When the browser fetches these over a cross-origin Tailscale URL (e.g. `https://macmini.tailf67cc5.ts.net/avatar/main`), the existing cookie-based session is not sufficient because the gateway uses token auth (not cookie-based sessions). The UI code also doesn't attach the Bearer token as a query parameter or Authorization header for these avatar requests.\n\nThe gateway's `authorizeControlUiReadRequest` already supports accepting auth via query parameter (`?token=<auth>`) through `resolveAssistantMediaAuthToken`, but the avatar route was not passing `allowQueryToken: true` to enable this fallback.\n\n## Fix\n\n1. **server-http.ts** — pass `allowQueryToken: true` to `handleControlUiAvatarRequest`\n2. **control-ui.ts** — accept `allowQueryToken` option and forward it to `authorizeControlUiReadRequest`\n3. **app-render.ts** — `buildAssistantAvatarRoute()` appends `?token=<auth>` when a token is available from the session auth state\n4. **app-render.helpers.ts** — new `resolveAvatarAuthToken()` helper to extract the token for avatar URL embedding\n\n## Testing\n\n```bash\n# Without token (returns 401 over cross-origin Tailscale URL):\ncurl https://macmini.tailf67cc5.ts.net/avatar/main\n\n# With token as query param (returns 200):\ncurl \"https://macmini.tailf67cc5.ts.net/avatar/main?token=<gateway-token>\"\n```\n\n\nFixes #85750\n\n---\n*Reported by @social5h3ll — fix by @social5h3ll via OpenClaw webchat*",
